column10:
If you look at the steam reviews for train simulator, you will find:

Negative:
70% of the people complaining about DLC;
30% of the people complaining about gameplay and errors;

Positive:
50% of the people denying all what is said above;
50% of the people that got train simulator for and kinda enjoy it.

Fact is, this game isn't for anyone. If you are a person that thinks trains are kinda fun and make funny sounds, this game is just a bit to complicated. You are not forced to buy the DLC. The game is "playable" without it, yes, the DLC is a bit overpriced, but once again, if you think it's ridicously expensive just don't buy it.

My conclusion: If you are a train fanatic, do buy this game. If you are looking for a neat little game that involves trains that go choo choo, don't buy train simulator. I spent many hours in this game and I still love it. So either buy the game or just leave and never come back.
